author: dlr
msg: Correct behavioral and performance problems of the 'svnmerge.py
(action_integrated): Look at the source URL when determing the
oldest revision, which is used to subtract revisions which pre-date
the branch (and thus can't have been "integrated").  Create a
RevisionSet object when doing the actual subtraction to avoid
N-squared performance from the RevisionSet.__sub__() method.
